column1: SIT1|FTTH-DG|Access_Supplier,Project_Reference,Home-id attributes are not being sent in SubmitOrder Request
column28:
Steps to Reproduce
1) Perform CheckServiceavailability with Address having Fibre Technology as FTTH-L2-BSA
2)Configure a Fibre Package
3) Add tariff
4)Proceed to checkout fill the customer details and in new connection section capture the Home-id
5)Proceed further and submit the order.


Actual Result
In the GenerateContract and Fulfillment modes
HOME_ID,ACCESS_SUPPLIER,Project_Reference values are not being sent as mentioned in the paths defined in user stories OS-34913,OS-34199


Expected Result
In the GenerateContract and Fulfillment modes
HOME_ID,ACCESS_SUPPLIER,Project_Reference values should be sent as mentioned in the paths defined in user stories.OS-34913,OS-34199


Note: Project_Reference and Home-id values are being sent in generatecontract mode
column50: 31/Jul/23 2:41 PM;sunil.kumar3@vodafone.com;Verify CheckServiceability, Checkout and SubmitOrder while doing New Fibre DG Acq with Home Id_Telsales.docx;https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/secure/attachment/1105151/Verify+CheckServiceability%2C+Checkout+and+SubmitOrder+while+doing+New+Fibre+DG+Acq+with+Home+Id_Telsales.docx
column546: New PCAT deployed
column1045: 03/Aug/23 1:11 PM;pallavi.chaudhari1@vodafone.com;Omnius Team is checking for this ;;;
column1046:
07/Aug/23 6:31 PM;sunil.kumar3@vodafone.com;We have gone through the issue and come to know that the issue is because PCAT configuration where the expression is not set correctly to  which will send above information related to Project_Reference,Home_id. 

We are sending ComponentAdditionalData of Project_Reference,Home_id the for the product FTTH-L2-BSA only during contract generate because the expression only results true during contract generate where we have the product under the cart but during the fulfillment the product will be moved to order.
 !screenshot-1.png|thumbnail! 
f we have product FTTH-L2-BSA-DTAG part of the cart then we would get the ComponentAdditionalData of Project_Reference,Home_id the for the product FTTH-L2-BSA-DTAG because the service expression results true for this product during order fullfilment.

In above scenario we have only FTTH-L2-BSA as part of cart not FTTH-L2-BSA-DTAG so we are sending ComponentAdditionalData of Project_Reference,Home_id the for the product FTTH-L2-BSA only during contract generate.

OSE is working as expected and no issue with s/w.

Please get this fixed or correct with VF PCAT team;;;
column1047: 07/Aug/23 6:33 PM;sunil.kumar3@vodafone.com;[~shuyan.luo@vodafone.com]: Can you please check this from your end as the FN mapper does not have correct information;;;

column1048:
19/Jul/23 5:38 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;Related to the error observed by comment https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OS-40559?focusedId=2859123&page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-2859123 that indicates a problem from the cables rules:

the version V2270_2023_07_00_038_D02 you are using is a development version that was provided by cable to OSF to test the development of NBA enhanced. If the OSF version on the environment does not implement the required interface changes it is expected to fail.

 

Related to the availability:

The availability for the given address ([https://wss-vf-dev1b.kabeldeutschland.de/VkdGatewayService/address/891367/availability?portal=OFT)] on the SIT1 backend (dev1b) is equal to the availability of the ACC1 backend (test1b) [The HAL Browser (kabeldeutschland.de)|https://wss-vf-test1b.kabeldeutschland.de/VkdGatewayService/hal-browser/browser.html#https://wss-vf-test1b.kabeldeutschland.de/VkdGatewayService/address/891367/availability?portal=OFT].

On the ACC1 however the availability is displayed correctly by OSF, so I don't think this is related to the availability itself.

 

It could be that OSF fails to display the availability if the cable plugin crashes, although I'm not sure why OSF would call the cable plugin before opening any package of the customer in the first place.

As it stands I don't see a reason why this is caused by an issue on the cable side. If the SIT1 environment does not contain a OSF version with the required NBA enhanced changes, then the Cable PCAT with version V2270_2023_07_00_038_D02 should not be used.;;;

Swagger UI (kabeldeutschland.de)

 

Please contact aonghus.mullins1@vodafone.com for any detailed questions with regards to the interface definition.

column1: SPIN does not exist for customer , authenticate via alternative data
column28:
Overview
This epic implements the use of the service PIN for Retail for Consumer cable customers (excluding converged/linked customers).

The service PIN is a 6-digit numerical code to authenticate cable customers. Customers have to be able to provide a randomly selected 2 digits from the stored PIN in order to be deemed authenticated. The logic for storing the PIN and requesting the random digits is provided by the Service PIN Engine (SPE). The functionality is similar to the Kundenkennwort change as implement in Fasttrack. The main difference is that for the Mobile Kundenkennwort, OSF determines the digits to be selected whereas here the SPE steers this flow. 

The SPE itself will be introduced within a separate project for the cable care hotline with a technical go-live in October 2022 (PPM ID 545188: Hotline Authentification Improvement).

The Service PIN shall be introduced in a phased approach based on BfDi priorities. The first steps related to this demand is:

Introduction Service Pin in Cable - B2C Sales in OSF
 

 

Current situation
Today we don’t have a safe / secure authentication method for cable customers because we don’t have a spoken password (Kundenkennwort) as we do have it for Mobile and DSL.

The agent only has the work instruction to ask for following attributes and the customer must correctly indicate 3 out of the 4 options.

Customer number
Postcode of the contracting party
Date of birth of the contracting party.
The last 4 digits of the IBAN.
Desired solution
For all B2C cable customers, the first method of authentication is the Service PIN. In case the service pin is incorrectly entered 2 times, the attempts are halted and the agent must use the procedural authentication as mentioned above (3 out of 4 ). 

Step 1: cable only customers (non-converged), including a cable customer linked with another cable customer  

User story steps -cable only in Retail
Happy flow
Agents searches customer data of Cable customer. The Cable customer can be a Unity Media or VKD customer, hosted in Solstice and/or other legacy systems (VKD/UM).  
OSF checks if customer has an active service PIN
SPE confirms active service PIN
OSF requests authentication for Service PIN
SPE sends Digit locations to be checked
customer provides digits
agents enters digits and sends to SPE
SPE checks digits and confirm correct authentication
System shows customer 360 View
agent continues salesflow
Alternative flow - Wrong PIN
Agents searches customer data of Cable customer
OSF checks if customer has an active service PIN
SPE confirms active service PIN
OSF requests authentication for Service PIN
SPE sends Digit locations to be checked
customer provides digits
agents enters digits and sends to SPE
SPE checks digits and denies authentication
OSF provides error info to the agent and requests to enter the PIN again
customer provides digits
agent enters digits and sends to SPI
SPE checks digits and denies authentication
OSF provides error info to the agent
Agents executes Alternative (3 of 4) authentication
System shows customer 360 view
agent continues sales flow
Alternative flow - No active PIN / No PIN set for customer
Agents searches customer data of Cable customer
OSF checks if customer has an active service PIN
SPE informs OSF that no active PIN is available for the customer.
OSF informs agent that no active PIN is available  or the PIN is not available for the customer yet.
Agent executes alternative (3 of 4)  authentication
system shows customer 360 view
agent continues sales flow
Alternative flow – SPE not available
Agents searches customer data of Cable customer
OSF checks if customer has an active service PIN
SPE is not available 
OSF informs agent that alternative authentication has to be used due to a technical issue.
Agents executes alternative authentication (3 of 4)
system shows customer 360 view
agent continues sales flow
 

Scope	 
Backends	 Wizard, Cablemaster(RNS), Solstice, UM, VKD
Customer Types	Consumer customers (including SoHo private)
Channels	Retail
 

Although only retail is in scope, other permissions that are assigned to telesales and other agents must also be taken into account as they impact the design of the new SPIN permission. For this purpose, the following rule should apply:

If the agent is forced to authenticate the customer at all and if so, at which point in the sales flow this should happen is determined by already existing permissions and functionalities outside this epic (such as: hard authentication, soft authentication, no authentication, flex authentication). The new permission for SPIN Authentication should not change that but only determine how authentication is executed when it is required. 

Related Demand:  [OSIP-1091] Correction of mTAN authentication mechanism - Vodafone Global Jira

There should not be any hardcoding done to design the flow for retail agents only. The design to restrict or allow certain agents should be based via the permissions as mentioned in OSIP-1091 and the new SPIN permission as implemented in the current Epic.  

 

 

Contact persons
 

E-mail	Dep.	Role
Claudia Maier	 	T3 PL Hotline authentication improvements
Maik Hildebrandt	 	Main Requestor (Trinity)
Kenan Guelen, Britta Hoffmann, 
Daniel Reckordt	 	Retail Business 
Benno Tietz	 	Privacy
Predrag Kukobat, Christian Wedershoven 	 	IT security
Alexander Stass	 	SPE 
Karin Decker, Kerstin Radke	 	Agent Desktop
Business Value
Increase the security and trust of our sales process

Cable (only) Customers : 9,1 Mio 

Estimated Risk:  1.130.000 €

Solution Hints
Webservice spec: https://de.confluence.agile.vodafone.com/pages/viewpage.action?spaceKey=DVD&title=Service+PIN
SPE should be called from Omnius
The Full service PIN should not be stored or visualized in any front-end. 
In case the Service PIN is entered incorrectly two times, The failed attempt has to be logged.  this functionality of logging failed attempts is NOT provided by the service PIN engine and has to be implemented in the front-end. (check design for other front-ends, example: agent desktop/cable master/cockpit)
Service PIN reset is not a functionality for OSF. (can be done in agent desktop / cockpit / RNS)

Estimated Risk:  1.130.000 €

Solution Hints
Webservice spec: https://de.confluence.agile.vodafone.com/pages/viewpage.action?spaceKey=DVD&title=Service+PIN
SPE should be called from Omnius
The Full service PIN should not be stored or visualized in any front-end. 
In case the Service PIN is entered incorrectly two times, The failed attempt has to be logged.  this functionality of logging failed attempts is NOT provided by the service PIN engine and has to be implemented in the front-end. (check design for other front-ends, example: agent desktop/cable master/cockpit)
Service PIN reset is not a functionality for OSF. (can be done in agent desktop / cockpit / RNS)

*PRECONDITIONS:*
1.Agent should not have soft authentication permission.
2.Agent has SPIN and FLEX permission.

column1: INT - TestPlan | OS-13847 | New sales of cable internet product via www lines (MVP) Part 2 Send to Fulfillment - Submit Order
column28:
h2. *Precondition*

OS-13839: Part 1: SOL1SE30 - SE-030 New sales of cable internet product via www lines (MVP) Part 1 until the end of the checkout - Vodafone Global Jira
h3. Desired Situation this EPIC

Enable the fulfilment capability so that the new Solstice customers ( which can be captured by the capability built by OS-13839) can be activated correctly through the Solstice backend processes. In general, the following should be enabled:
 * Send the product data configured by the agent in OSF configurator
 * Send the new checkout data which is required by the backend for the fulfilment of the orders related to the Solstice customers
 * Using of the specified solstice order structure (composite order interface)
 * Set order status for solstice orders
 * Update meta data for ContractSummary in OneDMS

h3. {color:#de350b}*Submit order:*{color}

Send the product related information for the technical provisioning. 

Send the checkout data which is required by the backend for the fulfilment of the orders related to the new Solstice customers:
 * required data for submit for the activation in Solstice 
 ** incl. red Sales ID
(Red sales id (VOID) should be send to Solstice as commissioning related sales id.)
 ** Delivery addresses for the hardware delivery need to be part of the composite order
 ** Payment details and customer data need to be part of composite order
 ** *VF-ID!!!* (OS-12220) Status 06.10. according to the current solution, the email address will be verified while confirming the contract summary in one click from the contract summary email. Therfore the VF-ID will be generated afterwards and internal ID of the VF-ID/eMail should be written into the composite order. (tbc if this should be included in this epic or in OS-12220)
 ** The region information (the contracting party of the customer VKD or UM) for the service address (UM footprint) should be part of the composite order for the new ACQ scenarios (it is sufficient to deliver a flag/indicator so that Solstice can differentiate between VKD and UM- sending 3 different values for UM-regions is not necessary)
 ** Order overview should be analysed regarding the display of "Neuer Anschluss" section and customer contact details (phone number type Telefon1 (only mobile) & Telefon 2 (mobile or fixedline)) and nationality (tbc)

The customer account id (incl. further customer and product data) shall not be written/persisted to/in the OGW index (-> might be covered via Sol0 - tbc)

Pending orders: if an order is still waiting for fulfillment, no addtional order can be created by opening an existing

column1: VF-DE || OSF || WAVE 8.1 || EPIC OS-28370 ||FTTH Wholebuy Deutsche Glasfaser (PPM 549498)- Test Plan
column28:
The aim of this project is to introduce new order capturing and order processing workflows for FTTH Wholebuy Deutsche Glasfaser (named _'FTTH DG' in this Epic)_ with alternative access supplier other than Telekom.  This includes setting up all related processes and IT systems to enable availability check, order capturing & fulfilment, activation, change use cases and clearings as well as customer operations, fault clearance, network and B2B invoice verification.

_note; 'Glasfaser ID' and 'Home ID' refer to the same item when mentioned in this epic - interchangeable_

 
h1. Business Scope
||Topic||Scoping||
|*Channel*|Telesales
COPS
Retail|
|*Customer*|New Customer
Existing Customer|
|*Line of business*|Consumer Customer (consumer tariffs)
SoHo Consumer|
|*Stacks*|Legacy DSL|
|*Portfolio*|Fiber (FTTH)|
|*Process Context*|Acquisition
Migration
ILS|
h1. TO BE Situation

This project is very similar to FTTH Wholebuy Telekom (see OS-17997). Some FTTH parts can be reused, other parts need newly implemented and other FTTH parts need a change.

*A. Product Catalogue (Ruling):*
 * {color:#172b4d}Reuse existing sales package category 'DSL & Glasfaser Produkte' (for FttH). Respective products will need to be added to these categories. VFP and prio result must indicate what is available.{color}
 * Product offers will be the same as the ones in the Wholebuy Telekom Epic
 ** Bandwidth will differ
 ** Hardware will differ
 * Catalogue ruling (filter, order) will be detailed out during design phase (via PPM team)
 * {color:#172b4d}Gigacombi must be posible for FttH DG{color}

*B. Availability check:*
 * {color:#172b4d}The existing icon "{*}GLAS{*}" should be visible on the Omnius Serviceability Bar also for FTTH-DG based on the current priority rules The color of this icon will be reflected by the "Rollout-status"{color} value.
 * New *Access Technology* integration required; {color:#172b4d}New parameter value:{color}{color:#172b4d}FTTH-L2-BSA{color}
 * New *Access Supplier* : value {color:#172b4d}DGW to be{color} received from VFP service.
 * In case of multi supplier possibility for a customer (edge case) --> there needs to be prioritisation of supplier towards agent and customer (logic already defined in Telekom epic)
 * {color:#172b4d}'Ausbaustatus' and logic. Below table is required for FTTH Wholebuy:{color}

 

!image-2023-04-05-14-03-11-364.png!

 
 * {color:#172b4d}*Additional request for FTTH GigaGemeinde - updates in VFP result/Color*  {color}
 * Note: This is a different logic than with FTTH Telekom and FTTH Deutsche Glasfaser
 ** Order are only allowed to be placed in OSF, when they are in the 'Standard sales phase'. 
 ** If case of a different phase, OSF receives the colors '{*}{color:#de350b}RED{color}{*}' and '{*}{color:#de350b}RED{color}{*}-{*}{color:#ff8b00}ORANGE{color}{*}', and it is not allowed to place an order.

!image-2023-02-23-13-45-33-225.png|width=569,height=192!
 * {color:#172b4d}AC must show relevant detailed information after check is completed (VFP must deliver this) --> Must be analog to the Wholebuy Telekom Epic (https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OS-17997){color}
 ** Regio Klasse
 ** Project-Referenz (Tender Area)
 ** Downstream/Upstream
 ** Leitungslieferant (Access Supplier)
 ** Ausbau Status

_See below 'scribble' for required AC output information (as done for FTTH Telekom)_

!image-2023-01-25-10-30-54-736.png|width=614,height=306!

 

*C. Customer 360 view* 
 * The _Access Supplier_ of the installed base product needs to be shown in Customer 360 view window for FTTH Bitstream customers (e.g. Telekom, Deutsche Glasfaser)

*D. Product Configurator/SC*
 * Agent must be able to manually create and configure the correct Sales package with FTTH DG products from the product configurator
 ** No NBA's will be used at go-live of FTTH DG

*E. Checkout:*
 * Glasfaser-ID (Home-ID) needs to be implemented as an additional checkout field
 ** Same field required in case of FTTH DG - Can be in similar location as Telekom 'Home ID' field, but has different validation logic!

 * 
 ** {color:#172b4d}Front-end field logic: free-text field of max 21 characters (TBD. which character set to be allowed, spaces to be allowed etc{color}).
 ** Whether there is a 'Home ID' even available at the time, is dependent on the 'Ausbaustatus' of FTTH DG
 *** {color:#172b4d}IF 'Ausbaustatus' = homesPrepared, homesReady or homesConnected i.e. VFP color towards OSF = Green, there CAN BE a 'Home ID' --> Field required in checkout but OPTIONAL {color}
 ** The field should be OPTIONAL - Agent can continue sale without the value.
 *** Needs to be supplied at a later stage outside of OSF via a clearing process (similar to Telekom)
 ** {color:#172b4d}IMPORTANT: If there is no "Home-ID" this will affect the wishdate option! See below for logic{color}
 * {color:#172b4d}IF there is NO Home-ID entered, and the agent wants to complete the checkout/move to the next step in OSF , there needs to be a pop-up message indicating to the agent that the Home-ID field is still empty and needs to be filled if possible.{color}
 ** {color:#172b4d}Similar to required message in https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OS-17997{color}
 ** {color:#172b4d}Message only needed if Home-ID can be available (Ausbaustatus){color}

_{color:#172b4d}see below for 'Home-ID' field logic (show or don't show){color}_
|*Scenario*|*Old > New*|*Behaviour Glasfaser-ID (HOME ID) field*|
|*Acquisition*|> FTTH DG|Target tariff is FTTH DG, existing tariff is non-FTTH, hence *show* Home-ID field|
|*Move Offnet*|Cable, FTTB > FTTH DG|Target tariff is FTTH DG, hence *show* Home-ID field
Same rules apply as defined for FTTH acquisition|
|*Migration*|FTTH DG > Cable, FTTB|Target tariff is not FTTH DG, hence do not show Home-ID field|
|*Package change*|FTTH DG > FTTH DG|(Bandwidth change within same FTTH provider) Old tariff is FTTH already, hence do not show Home-ID field.
GigaGemeinde <-> FTTH DG will not be allowed (by Ref. Data rulings and existing VFP priority logic handled by the main PPM project).|
|*Technology change*
*to* *FTTH*|DSL/LTE ZH > FTTH DG
 |Target tariff is FTTH DG, existing tariff is non-FTTH hence *show* Home-ID field
Same rules apply as defined for FTTH acquisition|
|*Technology change*
*from* *FTTH*|FTTH DG > DSL/LTE ZH|Target tariff is not FTTH DG, hence *do not show* Home-ID field*|
|*Booking of options*|n/a|Not relevant, *do not show* Home-ID field*|

 
 * *{color:#172b4d}Wish-date{color} (Wunschdatum)* logic based on below:
 -- IF Ausbaustatus = h{color:#172b4d}omesPrepared, homesReady or homesConnected{color} WITHOUT the Home ID entered = *15 working days*
 -- IF Ausbaustatus = h{color:#172b4d}omesPrepared, homesReady or homesConnected {color}WITH valid Home ID entered = *5 working days*
 -- IF Ausbaustatus = underConstruction, homesPassed, homePassedPlus, *Wishdate selection NOT possible*
 --- Then it will be ASAP in the backend
 -- {color:#172b4d}In scenario of 'Anbieterwechsel' then logic should be same as FTTH Telekom (ASAP, no wishdate selection possible){color}

_{color:#172b4d}see below for wunschdatum field logic (show or don't show){color}_
|*Scenario*|*Old > New*|*Wishdate Field*|
|*Acquisition*|> FTTH DG|show field|
|*Move offnet*|Cable, FTTB > FTTH DG|show field - rules as defined for acquisition FTTH DG |
|*Migration*|FTTH DG > Cable, FTTB|show - rules as defined for Cable acquisition |
|*Package change (ILS)*|FTTH DG > FTTH DG|not relevant - do +not+ show field|
|*Technology change*
*+to+ FTTH (ILS)*|DSL/LTE ZH > FTTH DG
 |not relevant - do +not+ show field|
|*Technology change*
*+from+ FTTH (ILS)*|FTTH DG > DSL/LTE ZH|not relevant - do +not+ show field|
|*Booking of options*|n/a |not relevant - do +not+ show section|
 * {color:#172b4d}Note: In case of ILS, wish-date selection is not possible (existing functionality).{color}

*F. Submit Order:*
 * {color:#172b4d}OGW must pass the value entered in the 'Glasfaser-ID' (Home-ID) field  to the backend in submitOrder.{color}
 * It must be accepted that value is 'empty' as Glasfaser-ID (Home-ID) can be empty in case if not available/not known
 * OGW value: In addition to Access Technology, we also need to submit the value 'Access Supplier', as there might be different legal texts. Below ID's come dynamically from the VFP, based on the VFP outcome (no hardcode):
 ** _Telekom ID: *DTAG*_
 ** _Deutsche Glasfaser ID: *DGW*_ 
 *** ID naming comes from the VFP, so content is irrelevant, mapping needs to be correct
 

 *G. Change{color:#172b4d} Scenarios{color}* 

The existing ILS, migration and move-offnet scenarios should consider the FTTH DG product and technology as well.  

 
*H. Roles & Permissions*
 * No (new) specific permissions or roles, all should be able to sell FTTH DG (Equal to Telekom Epic)
 * Ramp-Up will be controlled by VFP output and not roles/permissions
